Russian Army Academic Ensemble Gives Performance at KPA Unit 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The Russian Army Academic Song and Dance Ensemble named after Alexandrov on a visit to the DPRK gave a performance at a unit of the Korean People's Army Saturday.
 The performance began with a chorus of immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Il Sung" conducted by Russian People's Artist Byacheslav Korovko. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers sang well songs "Just War" and "We Will Serve Russia" and Russian folk song "Kalinka" which evoke ardent love of the country and surging hatred for the enemy among the Russian army and people, acclaimed by the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also put on the stage colorful dances including "Dance of Cossack Cavalrymen," "Holiday March Music" and "Let's Become Seamen", which showed beautiful rhythms and high skills. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They pleased the audience by impressively singing solo and chorus "Hero Was Eighteen Years Old," "My Native Home" and "Korea Is One" and other Korean songs popular among the Korean People's Army and people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The stage was beautifully decorated with world-famous songs including a song of the opera "Carmen." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 As a chorus of immortal revolutionary paean "Song of General Kim Jong Il" resounded through the theatre, the audience replied with a loud applause, hardening their will to accomplish the revolutionary cause of Juche under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance ended with chorus "Our Friendship Is Ever-lasting."

Radom Branch of Poland-Korea Association Formed 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- An inaugural ceremony of the Radom Branch of the Poland-Korea Association was held in Radom City on Sept. 4.
 Attending it were the representative of the PKA Central Committee, the chairman of the Opatuw Branch of the association and other public figures.
Rules of the Radom Branch were adopted and Artur Wepecky was elected as its chairman at the ceremony. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The chairman of the branch said that through various publications and DPRK homepage on Internet, they had better understanding of the Juche idea, the perfect unity of Korea where all the people are closely united around their leader and, especially, the Songun politics pursued by leader Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
We will work hard to develop the friendly relations with the Korean people through the activities of the branch, he stated. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He further said: President Kim Il Sung was a genuine leader of the people who devoted all his life to them. We are, indeed, envious of the Korean people being led by Kim Jong Il who is identical to the President. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He hoped that the Korean people would reunify the country under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il.

DPRK Fine Art Exhibition Opens in China 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Beijing, September 10 (KCNA) -- A DPRK fine art exhibition opened here on Thursday under the co-sponsorship of the Chinese Ministry of Culture and the DPRK embassy in Beijing.
 On display at the exhibition hall were more than 50 Korean paintings, graphic paintings, oil paintings and gold paintings, including a Korean painting portraying President   Kim Il Sung working at his office and a graphic painting showing leader Kim Jong Il among women soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the opening ceremony were Vice-Minister of Culture Meng Xiaosi and other officials concerned of China, working people in Beijing and DPRK Ambassador to China Choe Jin Su and embassy officials. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The exhibition will continue until September 19.

Chinese Art Troupe Gives Performance 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- The visiting Chinese art troupe gave a performance at the Mansudae Art Theatre on Sept. 11.
 Among the audience were soldiers of the Korean People's Army, artists and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A male solo "Words in mind", a female solo "A song resounding through the land", a female solo "Snow falling in northern China, I love you", a dance "Dance of lotus flower", a circus "Throwing bamboo bells" and others were acclaimed by the audience for their high level of representation and peculiar art talents. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers put on the stage Korean songs and music including a female solo of immortal famous song "A flower girl", a male solo "Sing, the fork from which the road to Mangyongdae branches off" and "A soldier is always near the General", a mixed duet "Arirang" and a concert of instrumental music "A bumper year of apple", which pleased the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance proceeded in an atmosphere overflowing with friendly feelings of the two peoples.

Kim Jong Il Receives Chinese Delegation 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 12 (KCNA) -- Kim Jong Il, general secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and chairman of the DPRK National Defence Commission, Sunday met the Chinese party and government delegation led by Li Changchun, member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China, on an official goodwill visit to the DPRK.
 Present were Li Changchun, Wang Jiarui, head of the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee, Ji Bingxuan, permanent vice-director of the Publicity Department of the CPC Central Committee, Sun Jiazheng, minister of Culture, Wu Donghe, Chinese ambassador e.p. to the DPRK, Liu Hongcai, deputy head of the International Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee, Wu Dawei, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, Gao Hucheng, vice-minister of Commerce, and other members of the delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand was Kang Sok Ju, first vice-minister of Foreign Affairs of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the meeting Li Changchun handed over a personal letter from Hu Jintao, general secretary of the CPC Central Committee and president of China, to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He also conveyed to him warm greetings of Jiang Zemin, chairman of the Central Military Commission of China. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Li presented a gift to Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Il expressed thanks for this and asked him to send his greetings to Hu Jintao and Jiang Zemin before conversing with him in an amicable atmosphere. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He had a luncheon with the guests on the same day.

Week of Russian Film Show Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- A week of Russian film show opened with due ceremony at the Central Workers Hall on Friday.
 Attending the ceremony were Vice-Minister of Culture Jo Chan Gu, officials concerned, creators and artistes in the field of culture and art, working people in the city of Pyongyang and Russian Ambassador to the DPRK Andrei Karlov and a Russian movie delegation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speeches were made there. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants appreciated a Russian feature film "Father and Daughter".

S. Korean Authorities' Pro-Japanese Humiliating Behavior under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The south Korean authorities shun the declassification of the documents related to the south Korea-Japan "agreement" adopted in 1965, reading the face of the outsiders though it is the era of giving importance to the nation, the era of reunification after the publication of the June 15 joint declaration. Rodong Sinmun Saturday in a signed commentary carried in this regard terms this attitude a contemporary form of treacherous, pro-Japanese humiliating behavior.
 The commentary says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean authorities are taking a double-dealing attitude. While recognizing the necessity to declassify the documents, they assert they cannot be opened to the public until the final ruling by a judicial institution under the pretexts of "diplomatic practices" and "relations with Japan." The declassification of the documents is not a matter to be decided upon in consideration of any diplomatic practices or by reading others' face as it pertains to the independent right of the south Korean authorities.
 Disclosing the reason why they are taking such a passive approach towards declassification of the documents related to the treacherous "agreement," the commentary goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Upset by the recent growing demand for the declassification in south Korea, the Japanese authorities threaten the south Korean authorities that if the latter declassify the documents they will also open to the public something not yet disclosed. So the south Korean authorities are now at a loss. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This clearly reveals the constitutional weakness of the present south Korean authorities who are not in a position to do what they wish, reading the face of outside forces, bereft of independent consciousness and political independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no ground for the south Korean authorities to shun opening the documents to the public as they are talking about the probe into the truth about past crimes. This issue is one of the basic problems showing whether the south Korean authorities have a will to totally eliminate the leftover of the Japanese imperialists' colonial policy or not. And it will also serve as a yardstick distinguishing the stand of giving importance to the nation from the stand of serving foreign forces.

KCNA Blasts U.S. Arms Buildup
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The United States is putting spurs to the preparations for a new war against the DPRK behind the curtain of dialogue.
 Recently the U.S. Defense Department decided to deploy 15 Aegis destroyers equipped with ultra-modern interceptor missile system in the East Sea of Korea and its surrounding waters till 2006 under the pretext of coping with "missile threat" from the DPRK. It is said that as its first phase two Aegis destroyers will be deployed in the East Sea of Korea and three in Hawaii soon on a permanent basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush bellicose forces made this decision not because of "missile threat" from someone. Their aim is to move their armed forces for a war of aggression to their operational areas and then round off at the final phase the preparations to mount a surprise preemptive attack on the DPRK on the entire front of the sea, the sky and the ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 South Korea and its vicinity have turned into a rendezvous, an operational base for the U.S. armed forces according to the "preemptive attack strategy" dubbed "Bush doctrine". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has begun the massive shipment of the latest war equipment worth nearly 13 billion U.S. dollars into south Korea under the signboard of "reduction" of its troops. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is busy with the move to merge the 13th Air Force Command in Guam with the 5th Air Force Command in Yokota Base of Japan and transfer the 1st U.S. Army Corps Command in Washington State to Kanagawa Prefecture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. bellicose forces have recently worked out and opened to the public "operation plan-5027-04," a scenario for the second Korean war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 All facts go to prove that the Bush administration's talk about the negotiated settlement of the nuclear issue between the DPRK and the U.S. is a sheer lie and it is leaving no means untried to round off its preparations for a preemptive attack on the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK will neither remain a passive onlooker to the U.S. frantic arms buildup nor wait with folded arms till the U.S. side has occupied its starting position after finishing its preparations for assault. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the Bush bellicose forces ignite a war despite the DPRK's warnings, they will face an unprecedented catastrophe.

Chinese Art Troupe Performs for Guests of Honor
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The visiting Chinese art troupe gave a performance for guests of honor at the Mansudae Art Theatre on Sept. 10.
 Among the audience were Kim Yong Nam, Yang Hyong Sop, Kim Kuk Thae and other senior party and state officials.
 Head of the Chinese art troupe Tian Junli and staff members of the Chinese embassy here were also among the audience. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The art troupe is made up of many first class artistes and international and national concours winners of the Chinese national art organizations that gave a special art performance in honor of leader Kim Jong Il during his unofficial visit to China in April. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A male solo "Sing, the Fork from which the Road to the Mangyongdae Branches off" and other numbers sang high praises of the immortal exploits performed by President Kim Il Sung who led the anti-Japanese revolutionary struggle to victory, thus achieving the historic cause of national liberation, and built a powerful socialist country, independent, self-supporting and self-reliant in national defence, on this land. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Through their male solo "A Soldier Is Always Near the General", a female solo "Red Flowers of Revolution in Full Bloom" and other Korean songs the Chinese artistes reflected the firm support and solidarity of the Chinese people to the Korean army and people in their efforts to bring about a high watermark of national prosperity under the Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also presented dance "Lotus Dance," mixed duet "We Drink Toast for Sake of Motherland" and other numbers reflecting the noble spiritual world of the Chinese people and the traditional lifestyle of different nationalities and famous dances of the world, beautifully decorating the stage. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performance was acclaimed by the audience for its great ideological value, the artistes' rich emotion and a high level of representation and perfect ensemble. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A floral basket was presented to them in congratulation of their successful performance.

"Anti-Terrorism War" Incites Anti-U.S. Sentiments Only
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The United States, which has resorted to high-handed practice and arbitrariness on the international arena, styling itself the world's lone superpower, is now finding itself isolated in the international community.
 The "anti-terrorism war" it started after the 9/11 incident has caused only anti-U.S. sentiments all over the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Bush administration, prompted by the gangster-like theory that the "anti-terrorism war" outside the U.S. borders would make the U.S. mainland more stable, perpetrated two criminal wars in the new century, going against the desire of humanity for the building of a peaceful world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. imperialists invaded Afghanistan in October 2001 and killed some 3,000 people in the country. And it attacked Iraq in March 2003 with the mobilization of hundreds of thousands of troops equipped with sophisticated weapons, alleging that they would bring "freedom" and "democracy" to the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 According to a report released by the U.S. Centre of Strategic and International Studies, more than 11,000 people were killed, at least 40,000 wounded and some 200 civilian facilities destroyed in Iraq as of June 18 this year since the outbreak of the war. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Though it unleashed the wars under the pretext of "fighting terrorism", the U.S. has still failed to find out Bin Laden's whereabouts and "weapons of mass destruction" in Iraq but revealed its brigandish nature only, inciting people's uprising in the two countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "war on terrorism", in the final analysis, has resulted in a vicious cycle of retaliation and terrorism, and in many countries including U.S. allies turning their back on the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Suffice it to say that demonstrations against the U.S. attempt to invade Iraq took place worldwide on an unprecedented scale last year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The demonstrations were participated in by 500,000 people in France, 600,000 in Germany, two million in Britain, three million in Italy and four million in Spain. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The 200,000-strong demonstration staged in Rome in early June this year against the U.S. "war on terrorism" touched off large-scale anti-U.S., anti-war demonstrations and rallies  in west European countries' capitals. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Besides, more and more countries' pullout of troops from Iraq has brought Iraq-based allied forces to a head. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has become a target of denunciation by world people desirous of peace and justice.

Spokesman for DPRK FM. on Issue of Uranium Enrichment in South Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- A spokesman for the Foreign Ministry of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea Saturday gave the following answer to a question put by KCNA as regards the cases of nuclear-related secret experiments disclosed in south Korea in succession recently:
 It has been brought to light recently that south Korea made a uranium enrichment experiment by laser in secrecy in 2000 and conducted an experiment for extracting plutonium in 1982. This has stirred up a big furor in the international community. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is strong suspicion that the disclosed experiments might be conducted at the instruction of the United States as they assume military nature. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has applied double standards as regards the nuclear issue. It has transferred nuclear technology to its "allies" and connived at their nuclear weapon-related activities and possession of nukes. But it has worked hard to stamp out nuclear activities for a peaceful purpose after faking up "misinformation" about the DPRK on account of its ideology and system. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 What matters is whether the U.S. intends to overlook south Korea's development of nuclear weapons as it did that of Israel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 South Korea is under U.S. nuclear umbrella. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is self-evident that the DPRK can never abandon its nuclear program under such situation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now employing sleight of hand to hush up the above-said cases. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We cannot but link these cases to the issue of resuming the six-party talks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The cases should be clarified transparently and thoroughly and necessary measures be taken. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will closely follow the expected results of the investigation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The international community should pay due attention to the disclosed issue of uranium enrichment in south Korea, not the non-existent "uranium enrichment issue" in the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the danger to be posed by the nuclear arms race in Northeast Asia is to be prevented, the U.S. should drop its hostile policy toward the DPRK in practice and opt for seeking an early negotiated settlement of the nuclear issue as justly demanded by the DPRK.

Spokesman for DPRK FM Supports Just Cause of Syria
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 11 (KCNA) -- The DPRK voices positive support and firm solidarity to the Syrian government and people in their just cause to defend the national dignity and the sovereignty of the country.
 A spokesman for the DPRK Foreign Ministry said this, answering the question put by KCNA as regards the recent increased pressure and military threat of the U.S. and Israel to Syria. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. is now putting unprecedented pressure on Syria. On September 2 it forced the UNSC to adopt a resolution calling for the withdrawal of Syrian forces from Lebanon as regards the issue of extending the term of the president in Lebanon.
 Timed to coincide with this, Israel has openly threatened to militarily strike Syria under the pretext of "eliminating" the leaders of the Palestinian resistance forces in Damascus and gone the lengths of "asking for international support." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. and the Israeli authorities do not conceal the fact that their anti-Syrian campaign is aimed to take Lebanon, a weak country, from Syria and force Lebanon to conclude a "peace treaty" with Israel. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The army and other armed forces of Syria are now getting fully ready for anti-U.S., anti-Israel war of resistance to safeguard the inviolable territory of the country and its national dignity from the U.S. escalating anti-Syria campaign. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. pressure and Israel's military threat to Syria are very dangerous moves to disturb the security and stability of Syria and hamstring the efforts to achieve fair and comprehensive peace in Mideast. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The prevailing situation which may trigger off a vicious cycle of ceaseless violence and terrorism in Mideast is arousing profound concern not only among the Mideast Arab countries but among the world peace-loving people.

North-South Joint Photo Exhibition Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mt. Kumgang resort, September 11 (KCNA) -- A north-south joint photo exhibition hailing the registration of Koguryo relics as the world's cultural heritage took place at Mt. Kumgang resort Saturday.
 On display there were 70 photos showing mural paintings of 15 tombs dating back to the period of Koguryo out of those registered as the world's cultural heritage in July. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there were historians, experts and personages of all social strata and officials concerned in the north and the south. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ri Ui Ha, deputy director of the Bureau for Direction of Cultural Preservation from the north, An Pyong U, professor at Hansin University from the south, and other speakers, said at the ceremony of opening the exhibition that the registration of Koguryo mural paintings as the world's cultural heritage is a great event of the nation as it means an international recognition of the academic and epic value of the historic relics of the Korean nation and the advantages of Korean national culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speaking at the ceremony, historians from the north and the south said that Koguryo was a sovereign state, adding that this is well illustrated by the description of King Tongmyong, the founder of Koguryo, as Sage King Tongmyong in "Historic Records of the Three Kingdoms", "Geographic Map in True Records of King Sejong" and other ancient documents. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koguryo, an imperial state, instituted and used its independent year and rejected foreign domination and interference and fully exercised its sovereign right, leading several principalities, they noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Koguryo mural paintings are estimated as artifacts important for the study of history as they are preserved better than any other relics. Mural paintings help know well about the unique and universal nature of Koguryo culture. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A joint communique was adopted at the opening ceremony. In the communique the historians of the north and the south agreed to deepen the researches into the Koguryo history and widely introduce this proud history to the whole world on the principle of national independence and historicism and thus make a positive contribution to establishing the Juche character of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants in the exhibition watched a documentary and a scientific film introducing the brilliant history and culture of Koguryo and enjoyed a performance given by an acrobatic troupe from the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A reception was given this evening in connection with the successful exhibition.
